<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000008#    01#        327.1#">Va. Code Ann. § 8.01-327.1</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_8.01-327.1"/><heading><desig>§ 8.01-327.1.</desig><title>Definition of "arrest under civil process."</title></heading><level levelType="paragraph"><bodyText><p>The terms <emphasis typeStyle="it">"arrest under civil process"</emphasis> and <emphasis typeStyle="it">"civil arrest"</emphasis> shall be synonymous and shall be the apprehending and detaining of a person pursuant to specific provisions of this title to achieve the following:</p></bodyText><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_1"/><heading><desig>1.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> A full and proper answer or response to interrogatories under <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 8.01-506"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 8.01-506">§ 8.01-506<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000008#    01#          506#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>;</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_2"/><heading><desig>2.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> His obedience to the orders, judgments, and decrees of any court.</p></bodyText></level></level><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p>1977, c. 617; 1984, c. 93.</p></bodyText></historyItem></historyGroup></history></level></statute></legislativeDocBody><metadata><dc:metadata xmlns: